stoneChat is a small LLM web chat for Windows XP-era machines and IE6.

Requirements
------------

PHP 5.4 is required. The launcher uses PHP's built-in web server:

  php -S

PHP 5.4:
https://windows.php.net/downloads/releases/archives/php-5.4.45-Win32-VC9-x86.zip

stunnel is also required. It provides the HTTPS layer for old Windows
systems.

stunnel:
https://www.stunnel.org/archive/5.x/stunnel-5.26-installer.exe

Configuration
-------------

Copy the sample config:

  CONF_SMP.INI -> CONF.ini

Then edit `CONF.ini` with Notepad. The file is heavily commented; the
comments are meant to be read from top to bottom.

Important sections:

  [User Admin]
    The default administrator user. It may edit configuration when
    allow_config is true and [ui] allow_online_editor is also true.

  [User Guest]
    The default guest user. It may log in but cannot edit configuration.

  [Model NAME]
    One complete usable model unit.

    NAME is the short model name used by allow_models and by the web
    model selector. The same section also contains API URL, API key,
    upstream model id, type, stream setting, max token limit, and timeout.

There is no separate Provider section. A model is the whole usable unit.
For example:

  [Model MiniMaxM3]
  active = 1
  label = MiniMax M3
  type = openai
  api_base = https://api.minimaxi.com/v1
  api_key = YOUR_MINIMAX_API_KEY_HERE
  model = MiniMax-M3
  stream = true
  max_tokens = 1024
  timeout = 60

Unused sample models may remain in `CONF.ini`, but set them to:

  active = 0

Inactive models are ignored by the loader and do not need real API keys.

Users control model access directly:

  allow_models = *

means all active models. Or list model names:

  allow_models = MiniMaxM3,GPT55

Running
-------

Double-click:

  RUN.cmd

If `CONF.ini` does not exist, `RUN.cmd` copies it from `CONF_SMP.INI`.

The launcher checks:

  PHP is available
  CONF.ini is valid
  the port is free or can be killed
  stunnel.exe exists
  cacert.pem exists
  HISTORY is writable

After startup, open:

  http://localhost:9999

